                            </li>
                            <li class="- topic/li ">
                                <p class="- topic/p ">The documentation updates for v1.0.4 include the following
                                        changes:<ul class="- topic/ul " id="unique_2_Connect_42_ul_aqv_kht_sbc" nd:nd-id="ul_aqv_kht_sbc">
                                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                                            <p class="- topic/p ">The topic of <xref class="- topic/xref " href="#unique_3" type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>Creating RMF data sources<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">To access RMF Monitor III metrics in Grafana, you need to connect to the <ph class="- topic/ph ">Distributed Data Server</ph> (<ph class="- topic/ph ">DDS</ph>) by         adding an RMF data source.</desc></xref>
                                                has been updated as per the new UI changes.</p>
                                        </li>
                                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                                            <p class="- topic/p ">The <xref class="- topic/xref " href="#unique_4" type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>Upgrading the RMF for z/OS plugin on Grafana<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">You must ensure that the <ph class="- topic/ph ">IBM RMF for z/OS Grafana</ph> plugin is up         to date to leverage its enhanced functionalities. You can do so by either installing or         upgrading to the latest version of the plugin.</desc></xref> topic is
